# API Layer

## HTTP client

- **Only** use `apiClient` from `src/shared/lib/axios.ts` — no raw `fetch()` calls anywhere
- Auth token attachment and refresh handled by interceptors in `axios.ts` — API functions **never** manually set `Authorization` headers

## File placement

- Feature API functions live in `src/features/<name>/api/<feature>-api.ts`
- Export typed async functions — components and hooks import from here, not axios directly

## Naming convention (verb-first)

```typescript
getBookings(params: ApiListParams)
getBookingById(id: string)
createBooking(data: CreateBookingInput)
updateBookingStatus(id: string, status: BookingStatus)
deleteBooking(id: string)
```

- `get*` for reads, `create*` for POST, `update*` for PATCH/PUT, `delete*` for DELETE
- Return typed promises — use shared types from `src/shared/types/api.ts` and feature `types/`

## Environment

- Base URL from `src/shared/config/env.ts` (`VITE_API_URL`) — never hardcode URLs
